# Write Your First Program in C++

This repository is a beginner-friendly guide to writing your first program in **C++**. If you're just starting your programming journey, this tutorial will help you understand the basics of C++ and get you started with coding.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have:

1. A C++ compiler installed on your system (e.g., GCC, Clang, or MSVC).
2. A code editor or IDE (e.g., Visual Studio Code, Code::Blocks, or Dev-C++).
3. Basic knowledge of how to use a terminal or command prompt.

---

## üìã Steps to Write Your First C++ Program

### Step 1: Set Up Your Environment
1. Install a C++ compiler if you don't already have one. [Click here for installation instructions](https://www.cplusplus.com/doc/tutorial/introduction/).
2. Choose an editor or IDE for writing your code.

---

### Step 2: Write Your First Program
Create a file named `hello_world.cpp` and add the following code:

```cpp
#include <iostream> // Include library for input and output

int main() {
    std::cout << "Hello, World!"; // Print "Hello, World!" to the console
    return 0; // Indicate that the program executed successfully
